headline: CoStar raises annual revenue forecast as net bookings climb
summary: Real estate information provider CoStar Group raised its annual revenue forecast on Tuesday, aided by increased net new bookings and consumer traffic on its Homes.com website. The company benefits as both customers and real estate agents turn to its platform, which features a comprehensive commercial real estate database. Users gain access to detailed property listings, leasing and sales information, tenant profiles and up-to-date demand statistics.

headline: CoStar’s (NASDAQ:CSGP) Q2 Sales Top Estimates
summary: Real estate data provider CoStar Group (NASDAQ:CSGP) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 15.3% year on year to $781.3 million. The company expects next quarter’s revenue to be around $802.5 million, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.17 per share was 23.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
